            Valentina 许佳 is a junior studying Hotel Administration at Cornell University. Originally born and raised in China, she went to a boarding school in Ohio at 14. Later on, her family moved to Long Island, NY.<br></br>

The inspiration for starting Bridging Pacific came when she spent her semester at home with her mom and younger brother. While handling schoolwork, she helped her family with the immigration process, younger brother with applying to high school, and little things such as setting up an auto-payment for water bills online. She discovered that there was not a centralized place where first-generation immigrants could find resources for support. She then decided to co-found Bridging Pacific and build a resource bank and community to provide support for immigrant families.<br></br>

With Bridging Pacific, she wants to first create a resource bank for Chinese immigrant parents and ease their navigation of life in North America. She also hopes to create a community for immigrant children and support their academic and professional growth. In the long term, she hopes the immigrant community building will expand globally and become “Bridging World”

